IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: To provide funding to build and sustain the infrastructure of the John A. Burns School of Medicine and its departments: fund research, education, and scholarly development; provide additional resources to recruit, retain, and develop qualified faculty at the University of Hawaii; provide clinical training and education to students of the University of Hawaii, and provide health care to the general public, with special attention to the poor and other underserved populations of Hawaii and the Pacific region.
IRS990.MissionDescription: UCERA is a non-profit organization established to further the mission and vision of the John A. Burns School of Medicine at the University of Hawaii (JABSOM). It contributes to JABSOM's goal of improving the health care status of the citizens of Hawaii and the Pacific by supporting the education, research and clinical activities of the School. It supports financial diversification of the School by developing revenue generating initiatives in collaboration with hospitals, government agencies and other entities.
IRS990.Description: Clinical and professional services - 1) provide health care to the general public, with special attention to the poor and other underserved populations of Hawaii and the Pacific Region. 2) Specialty Clinics - multi-specialty faculty practice at clinics located at various sites. 3) Queen's Hospital and Hawaii Pacific Health/Kapiolani Hospital Contracts - provide faculty members to treat patients and to provide specialty clinical services to hospitals. 4) Veteran's Administration Specialty Clinics - provide specialist physicians to treat patients at the VA Medical & Regional Outpatient Clinic. This population tends to be indigent and underserved. The VA Clinic is also a teaching site for the University of Hawaii John A. Burns School of Medicine and provides a base of teaching patients.

Activity2.Description: Medical School and Faculty Support - Provide funding to build and sustain the infrastructure of the University of Hawaii John A. Burns School of Medicine and its Departments. Provide additional resources to recruit, retain, and develop qualified faculty at the University of Hawaii Medical School.

Activity3.Description: Research Support - Project Title-Transformative Learning: Patterns of Psychophysiologic Reponse in Technology Enabled Learning and Intervention Systems. This research hypothesizes that biometric data can identify and predict the arousal patterns associated with tobacco use behavior, and that patterns of cue reactivity will allow is to differentiate between psychological and physiological arousal in smokers.

ActivityOther.Description: Educational Support - 1) provide education and clinical training for the University of Hawaii Medical School students. 2) International Training Program - provide international medical students and residents with U.S. training experiences at the University of Hawaii John A. Burns School of Medicine. 3) Dean-Standardized Patients - provide simulated patients for clinical skills training and examinations for School of Medicine students and residents.
